<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="passage-n">passage <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pæsɪdʒ/    美 /'pæsɪdʒ/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>[正式用语] 经过；通过</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the passage of the Act
法案的通过</p><footer>2021新高考改</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-corridor">2.★ <strong>通路；通道；走廊 (corridor)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The passage through the mountains is dangerous. 
那条山路很危险。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(书、乐曲等的) 章节；段落：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Ruth read us a passage from the Bible. 
鲁思给我们读了一段《圣经》。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>(乘船的) 航程：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My parents couldn’t afford the passage to America.
我父母付不起去美国的船费。</p></div></div>